2016-01-11:   1.1.1:
--------------------
  * look for MKL in sys.prefix/Library on Windows


2015-10-02:   1.1.0:
--------------------
  * The mem_stat function only returned the number of bytes allocated and
    took an integer that was unused.  It now returns a tuple containing the
    number of bytes allocated and the number of blocks allocated.
  * The get_cpu_clocks function now casts from an unsigned long long.
  * The single library mkl_rt is linked against, to allow runtime selection
    of the threading model.
  * updated the update_readme.py script to run on Python 3


2013-04-29:   1.0.0:
--------------------
  * initial release
